# **1. What We Are Building**

FORGE is an AI builder marketplace. It connects two underserved audiences: entrepreneurs who have built apps, tools, and automations using AI coding tools (Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, Lovable, Bubble) and want to monetise their work — and small businesses that need affordable AI-powered tools but cannot justify agency or developer costs.

## **1.1 The Core Value Proposition**

| **FOR SELLERS (Builders)** | **FOR BUYERS (SME Owners)** |
| --- | --- |
| Submit your product URL — AI generates a full sales page automatically | Browse 300+ AI-built tools by business function |
| Sell licensed (multi-buyer recurring) or exclusive (one buyer) versions | Try free trials, watch demos, test sandboxes before buying |
| Earn passive income or sell the full business via Flippa integration | Buy working tools for £49–£1,200 instead of £5,000–£50,000 agency quotes |
| Free to list — FORGE takes 15% commission on sales only | No technical skills needed — no-code setup wizard included |

## **1.2 Product Scope — What Claude Code Will Build**

The MVP is scoped to one critical pipeline: the Seller Onboarding and AI Sales Page Generation flow. This is the supply-side engine that makes the marketplace viable. Everything else depends on it working.

- Seller registers and creates a profile (Supabase Auth + Webflow/Framer)

- Seller submits their product URL via a form

- Platform crawls the URL via Firecrawl API and extracts structured content

- Claude API generates a full buyer-facing sales page from the extracted content

- Seller reviews and edits the draft, then publishes the live listing

- Buyer views the public product page, tries a demo, and purchases

## **1.3 Flippa Integration (Phase 2)**

FORGE integrates with Flippa.com — the world's largest online business marketplace. Sellers can cross-list products on Flippa for additional exposure, or initiate a full business sale/auction. This is a Phase 2 feature. Do not attempt to build this in the MVP sessions.

