# **4. Database Schema (Supabase)**

The following tables form the complete MVP database. Paste the Claude Code prompt below into Session 1 to generate the full SQL migration automatically.

## **4.1 Tables Overview**

| **Table** | **Purpose** | **Key Fields** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| sellers | Seller profiles linked to Supabase auth users | id, user_id, display_name, bio, avatar_url, tool_tags[], stripe_account_id, verified |
| products | Product listings — all states (draft/live/archived) | id, seller_id, title, tagline, description, features (jsonb), screenshots[], price_licensed, price_exclusive, status |
| sales_pages | AI-generated copy for each product listing | id, product_id, headline, subheadline, body_copy, cta_primary, meta_title, meta_description, published_at |
| purchases | Buyer transaction records | id, buyer_id, product_id, purchase_type (licensed/exclusive), amount, stripe_payment_id, created_at |
| reviews | Buyer ratings and written reviews | id, product_id, buyer_id, rating (1-5), body, created_at |
| error_log | Make/n8n automation failures for debugging | id, scenario, payload, error_message, created_at |

## **4.2 Session 1 Prompt — Generate Full Schema**

**COPY AND PASTE THIS ENTIRE PROMPT INTO CLAUDE CODE SESSION 1**

| I am building an AI marketplace called FORGE. My stack is: - Database + Auth: Supabase (free tier) - Frontend: Framer - Automation: n8n self-hosted on Railway - AI: Claude API (Anthropic) - Scraping: Firecrawl - Email: Resend - Payments: Stripe Task: Generate a complete Supabase SQL migration file for the FORGE MVP. Create these tables with appropriate column types, constraints, and Row Level Security (RLS) policies: 1. sellers (id uuid PK, user_id uuid FK auth.users, display_name text,    bio text, avatar_url text, tool_tags text[], stripe_account_id text,    verified boolean default false, created_at timestamptz default now()) 2. products (id uuid PK, seller_id uuid FK sellers, title text NOT NULL,    tagline text, description text, features jsonb, use_cases jsonb,    screenshots text[], demo_url text, video_url text,    price_licensed numeric, price_exclusive numeric,    status text CHECK status IN ('draft','live','archived') default 'draft',    created_at timestamptz default now()) 3. sales_pages (id uuid PK, product_id uuid FK products UNIQUE,    headline text, subheadline text, problem_statement text,    body_copy jsonb, cta_primary text, cta_secondary text,    meta_title text, meta_description text, published_at timestamptz) 4. purchases (id uuid PK, buyer_id uuid FK auth.users,    product_id uuid FK products, purchase_type text,    amount numeric, stripe_payment_id text, created_at timestamptz default now()) 5. reviews (id uuid PK, product_id uuid FK products,    buyer_id uuid FK auth.users, rating int CHECK rating BETWEEN 1 AND 5,    body text, created_at timestamptz default now()) 6. error_log (id uuid PK, scenario text, payload jsonb,    error_message text, created_at timestamptz default now()) RLS rules: - sellers: owners can read/write their own row. Public can read verified=true rows. - products: sellers can CRUD their own. Public can SELECT where status='live'. - sales_pages: sellers can CRUD via their product. Public can read published. - purchases: buyers can read their own. Sellers can read purchases of their products. - reviews: anyone authenticated can insert. Public can read. - error_log: service_role only. Output: a single .sql file I can run in the Supabase SQL editor. |
| --- |

# **5. n8n Automation — Core Workflow**

The heart of the MVP is a single n8n workflow that fires when a seller submits a product URL. It chains four API calls: Firecrawl (scrape) → Claude API (generate) → Supabase (store) → Resend (notify). Claude Code will build and test this workflow in Session 5.

## **5.1 Workflow Map**

| **Step** | **Node Type** | **Service** | **Action** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Webhook Trigger | n8n | Receives POST from Framer form: { seller_id, product_url, name, category, description } |
| 2 | HTTP Request | Firecrawl API | POST /v1/scrape — returns markdown content + screenshot URL from product URL |
| 3 | IF Node | n8n Logic | Check markdown length > 500 chars. If false: skip to error branch, email seller for manual input |
| 4 | HTTP Request | Anthropic API | POST /v1/messages — sends system prompt + scraped content, returns structured JSON sales page |
| 5 | HTTP Request | Supabase REST | POST /products — insert product row with status=draft |
| 6 | HTTP Request | Supabase REST | POST /sales_pages — insert AI-generated copy linked to product_id |
| 7 | HTTP Request | Resend API | POST /emails — send 'Your draft is ready' email to seller |
| 8 | HTTP Request (Error) | Supabase REST | On any failure: POST /error_log with scenario name + payload + error |

## **5.2 The Claude API System Prompt (Sales Page Generator)**

This is the most important prompt in the entire build. It transforms raw scraped content into structured buyer-facing sales copy. Store this in an n8n credential or environment variable — do not hardcode it.

**SYSTEM PROMPT — PASTE EXACTLY INTO N8N HTTP NODE BODY**

| You are a senior SaaS copywriter for FORGE, a marketplace where AI builders sell apps and tools to small businesses. Your job is to write compelling, clear, and honest sales page copy from raw product content. AUDIENCE: SME business owners who are NOT technical. Write for them. TONE: Direct, benefit-led, jargon-free. No hype. Focus on outcomes. OUTPUT: Return valid JSON ONLY. No preamble. No markdown backticks. {   "headline": "8-12 words. Benefit-led. Not feature-led.",   "subheadline": "20-30 words elaborating the core benefit.",   "problem_statement": "2-3 sentences about the pain this solves.",   "features": [{ "title": "short", "description": "1-2 sentences" }],   "use_cases": ["3-5 short scenarios of who uses this and why"],   "cta_primary": "Action verb + benefit. Max 5 words.",   "cta_secondary": "Softer secondary action. Max 5 words.",   "meta_title": "SEO title under 60 chars.",   "meta_description": "SEO description under 155 chars." } |
| --- |

**USER MESSAGE TEMPLATE — DYNAMICALLY POPULATED BY N8N**

| Product Name: {{ $json.product_name }} Product URL: {{ $json.product_url }} Category: {{ $json.category }} Seller's Description: {{ $json.seller_description }} Crawled Content: {{ $json.scraped_markdown }} Generate the sales page JSON now. |
| --- |

# **6. The 8 Claude Code Sessions**

The MVP build is divided into 8 independent Claude Code sessions. Each session has one objective, one deliverable, and one test that must pass before you move to the next session. Do not combine sessions. Do not skip sessions.

|  | How to start each session: Open a new Claude Code conversation. Paste the opening context block from Section 7 first. Then paste the session-specific prompt below. This gives Claude Code the project context it needs every time. |
| --- | --- |

| **1** | **Supabase Foundation — Schema + Auth** Run the SQL migration from Section 4.2. Enable email auth. Test by creating a user via Supabase dashboard. Confirm all 6 tables exist with correct columns and RLS policies active. DONE WHEN: SQL runs without errors + test user appears in auth.users. |
| --- | --- |

| **2** | **Framer Site Structure** Create a Framer project. Set up 5 page templates: Home, Product Listing (CMS), Seller Profile (CMS), Seller Dashboard, Registration. Connect custom domain. DONE WHEN: 5 pages exist, domain connected, CMS collections created for Products and Sellers. |
| --- | --- |

| **3** | **Seller Registration Flow** Build the Framer registration page. Embed Supabase Auth JS via Framer custom code. On successful signup, create a row in the sellers table via Supabase API. DONE WHEN: Test user registers via the Framer page and appears in both auth.users and sellers tables. |
| --- | --- |

| **4** | **Product Submission Form** Build the Framer product submission form. Fields: product URL, name, category (dropdown), short description. On submit, POST to n8n webhook URL. DONE WHEN: Form submits, n8n webhook receives the payload, visible in n8n execution log. |
| --- | --- |

| **5** | **n8n Workflow — Firecrawl + Claude API** Build the full n8n workflow from Section 5.1. Steps 1-4: Webhook → Firecrawl → length check → Claude API. Test with 3 real product URLs. DONE WHEN: 3 URLs produce valid JSON sales page output from Claude API, visible in n8n execution log. |
| --- | --- |

| **6** | **n8n Workflow — Supabase Write + Email** Add steps 5-8 to the n8n workflow: write to products table → write to sales_pages table → send email via Resend → log errors. DONE WHEN: Supabase rows created with correct data + Resend email arrives in your inbox. |
| --- | --- |

| **7** | **Seller Draft Review Interface** Build the Framer seller dashboard page that reads the draft sales page from Supabase. Seller can edit headline, subheadline, CTA, and pricing. Save button updates Supabase. Publish button sets status to 'live'. DONE WHEN: Editing and publishing works end-to-end in a browser. |
| --- | --- |

| **8** | **Public Product Listing Page** Build the public Framer product page template connected to the Supabase products + sales_pages tables. Renders: headline, features, screenshots, pricing, seller profile, CTA buttons. DONE WHEN: A live product URL loads correct content from the database. |
| --- | --- |

