**COPY THIS BLOCK — PASTE AT THE START OF EVERY CLAUDE CODE SESSION**

| PROJECT CONTEXT — FORGE AI Marketplace ====================================== I am building FORGE — an AI builder marketplace where developers sell AI-built apps and tools to small businesses. I am non-technical. I need step-by-step instructions I can follow without writing code myself. Explain every action clearly. MY TECH STACK: - Frontend / CMS: Framer (free tier) - Database + Auth: Supabase (free tier)   URL: [YOUR SUPABASE URL]   Anon Key: [YOUR ANON KEY] - Automation: n8n self-hosted on Railway   n8n URL: [YOUR N8N URL] - AI generation: Claude API (Anthropic)   Key: [YOUR ANTHROPIC API KEY] - Web scraping: Firecrawl   Key: [YOUR FIRECRAWL KEY] - Email: Resend   Key: [YOUR RESEND KEY] - Payments: Stripe   Keys: [YOUR STRIPE KEYS] - Domain: [YOUR DOMAIN] - GitHub repo: forge-mvp (private) DATABASE TABLES ALREADY CREATED: sellers, products, sales_pages, purchases, reviews, error_log (See schema in GitHub repo: /supabase/migrations/001_initial.sql) BUILD APPROACH: - No custom backend code unless absolutely necessary - Use n8n for all automation logic - Use Supabase REST API for all data reads/writes - Use Framer for all frontend — custom code embeds where needed CURRENT SESSION GOAL: [REPLACE THIS WITH THE GOAL FROM THE SESSION YOU ARE STARTING] |
