# **8. Quick Prompt Library**

These are ready-to-use Claude Code prompts for common tasks you will encounter during the build. Each can be pasted directly after the opening context block.

## **8.1 Supabase — Fetch Products for Framer**

| Write a JavaScript fetch call I can embed in a Framer custom code component to load all products where status='live' from my Supabase products table. Include the seller display_name from the sellers table via a join. Return the results sorted by created_at descending. Use my SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY environment variables. Show me exactly where to paste this in Framer. |
| --- |

## **8.2 n8n — Debug a Failed Execution**

| My n8n workflow failed at step [STEP NAME]. Here is the error log entry from my Supabase error_log table: [PASTE ERROR HERE] My n8n workflow processes: Webhook → Firecrawl → Claude API → Supabase → Resend. Diagnose the failure and give me the exact fix to apply in n8n. |
| --- |

## **8.3 Framer — Build a CMS-Connected Component**

| Build a Framer custom code component that displays a product card. It should accept these props: title, headline, price_licensed, price_exclusive, category, screenshot_url, seller_name. Style it with a dark (#1A1C24) background, amber (#E8920A) accent, Syne font for headings, clean minimal layout. Show me the complete component code and how to add it to Framer. |
| --- |

## **8.4 Stripe — Create a Payment Link for a Product**

| I need to add a Stripe payment flow to FORGE. When a buyer clicks 'Buy Licence' on a product page, they should be sent to a Stripe Checkout session. Using n8n, create a workflow that: 1. Receives a POST with: product_id, buyer_email, purchase_type (licensed/exclusive) 2. Looks up the price from Supabase products table 3. Creates a Stripe Checkout session via the Stripe API 4. Returns the checkout URL to redirect the buyer After payment success, record the purchase in the Supabase purchases table. Show me the complete n8n workflow configuration. |
| --- |

## **8.5 Resend — Custom Email Template**

| Create an HTML email template for FORGE to send when a seller's AI-generated draft listing is ready to review. Branding: dark background (#0C0B09), amber accent (#E8920A), clean sans-serif font, FORGE logo as text. Email should include: - Subject: 'Your FORGE listing draft is ready — [Product Name]' - Seller's first name personalisation - Product name and thumbnail (if available) - Clear CTA button: 'Review Your Draft' linking to dashboard URL - Estimated review time: 5 minutes - Footer with unsubscribe link Format for use with Resend API in n8n. Show me the complete HTML and the n8n HTTP node configuration to send it. |
| --- |

